article.description: Howard leads Southern past Ark-Pine Bluff 51-36
article.headline: Howard leads Southern past Ark-Pine Bluff 51-36
article.linkText: Howard leads Southern past Ark-Pine Bluff 51-36
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- Austin Howard threw three touchdown passes to lead Southern to a 51-36 victory over Arkansas-Pine Bluff on Saturday night. Howard's first pass was a 79-yard TD strike to Reggie Travis on the second play of Southern's (3-3, 2-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference) opening drive. Arkansas-Pine Bluff (1-4, 0-3) answered when Antonio Jenkins sacked Howard, causing a fumble that Kyle Walker punched in for a touchdown. Danny Johnson returned the ensuing kickoff 98 yards for a touchdown to give the Jaguars a 14-7 lead. The Golden Lions answered again when Benjamin Anderson ran for a 1-yard score to tie it at 14. Howard had TD passes of 11 and 27 yards in the second quarter, and wide receiver Willie Quinn threw a 41-yard touchdown pass to Travis to give Southern a 41-21 lead in the third quarter. Travis finished with five catches for 156 yards and three touchdowns.
